    <briefdescription>
<para>Base class for all comparison operators used in the math engine. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Comparison operators evaluate two floating point values and return a boolean result indicating whether the comparison condition is met. These operators are typically used by logical or conditional nodes inside the formula graph. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
